				<p>I used half as much cream, but it wasn&#8217;t quite enough. 3/4 the called for cream worked great.</p>
<p>Also, if your white chocolate ganache separates, reheat it and stir more thoroughly as it cools. That will help bring it back together. We did this, adding a bit more cream to make the result less firm, and it came together nicely.</p>
<p>I definitely agree that 1 teaspoon of mint was just right. More would have overwhelmed the chocolate.</p>
