<li class="commentbody" id="comment-718232">
			<cite>Anne</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-718232" title="">June 12, 2011</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">104</div>

				<p>I used Callebaut white chocolate, but I still had terrible separation. The ganache was a gloppy ball of greenish chocolate in a vat of oil. As per the suggestion by Michael L, i reheated it, added a touch more cream, and stirred the c**p out of it. That seems to have solved the problem. Yum!<br />
Definitely considering replacing the mint with hazelnut syrup next time.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-721709">
