<li class="commentbody" id="comment-904435">
			<cite>Gemma</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-904435" title="">September 8, 2011</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">106</div>

				<p>Hi Deb,<br />
I made these brownies the other day at work and even though I thought the required amount of flour was less than it should have been, I followed your recipe exactly. The brownies tasted delicious, but it was the consisitency of &#8220;brownie batter&#8221; you&#8217;d find in ice cream. I was just wondering if 3/4 cup of flour was a possible typo?<br />
Also, the amount of batter I made from your recipe was only enough for a 10&#8243;x 6&#8243;x 4&#8243; pan (1/2 a 4&#8243; hotel pan) and the yield you gave read 72 normal brownies and 117 1&#8243; brownies; I got 12 brownies. I&#8217;m not complaining by any means, just making sure if I read the recipe right or not.<br />
Thanks!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-1311286">
